race.comment: Tricky. GLIMMERINTHEDUST (4) debuts owning two sharp trials at Lark Hill. Has an awkward gate, but she has the blinkers on, and he looks good enough to manage. As with her fellow debutants, the betting will be key. LIKE CLOCKWORK (8) has also performed well at the trials. CJP has been aboard all three and rides today. The gate is a bit sticky, but on what we've seen, she can feature. SOPHISTRY (12) found a place in the second of the two Lark Hill trials and debuts with the top jockey engaged. That's a decent push for her chances, and she maps for the run of the race. WHY SHE STAYED (5) trialled well and resumed with a 1.5L defeat at Northam. She will be fitter and is still shy of her best. Has the race fitness and can make the finish with average luck from the outside gate.
